Based on the modern theory of polarization, the linear piezoelectric effect (dijk) of a flat 2D material can be calculated by evaluating the change in polarization under uniaxial strains (eijk). The third-rank piezoelectric tensors eijk and dijk can be evaluated by their respective Maxwell relations [71]:2.6eijk=dPidεjkdijk=dPidσjk\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
